1. Bank of America: US high-yield bonds have seen the largest weekly outflow of funds in history;
2. Curve founder: once again extended the lock-up period of veCRV held to 4 years;
3. FTX/Alameda address unpledged 186,000 SOL, worth about 21.56 million US dollars;
4. Trader Eugene: The upward trend of 10-year US Treasury yields may trigger real-level risks;
5. North Carolina proposes to allow the use of crypto assets to pay taxes;
6. Trump family crypto project WLFI denies selling ETH;
7. Since January 2021, the supply of stablecoins on the ETH mainnet has increased by more than 5 times, reaching 123 billion US dollars;
8. The decoupling of sUSD is due to the change of the SIP-420 mechanism, not a bad debt problem;
9. The Ministry of Finance: Adjust the prescribed tariff rate from 84% to 125%;
10. Moody's chief economist: Inflation data will be "very ugly" by this summer;
11. Spot gold hits the $3,230/ounce mark;
12. US prosecutors say the Justice Department's adjustment of encryption policy does not affect the charges against Do Kwon.
